本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:陳柏儒研究生(外文):Chen, Po Ju論文名稱:南管二絃《八駿馬》演奏探討論文名稱(外文):Nanguan Erxian Performance Study of Ba Jun Ma指導教授:鄭德淵、歐光勳學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立臺南藝術大學系所名稱:民族音樂學研究所學門:藝術學門學類:音樂學類論文出版年:2013畢業學年度:101語文別:中文論文頁數:146中文關鍵詞:南管、八駿馬、二絃、演奏語法外文關鍵詞:nanguan、Bajunma、erxian、performance gramma相關次數:

被引用:0點閱:458評分:下載:0書目收藏:0



本文以南管二絃為主要研究對象，透過南管譜《八駿馬》探討二絃的加花與演奏技法的使用。《八駿馬》為南管四大譜「四、梅、走、歸」中的「走」，為「走馬」也稱作《八駿馬》，為南管二絃的代表曲目。因南管二絃的樂器形制與物理特性，演奏者發展出一套獨特的演奏規範，而《八駿馬》一曲即充分的展現二絃的演奏語法。本文首先介紹南管的管門、工ㄨ譜的譜字與二絃的演奏規範。接著分析《八駿馬》的動機的組合與連結使用與旋律的架構與特徵，瞭解旋法特徵並結合音階概念，對於演奏時加花與技巧能更有邏輯性的做使用。第三章使用比較方法，檢視《八駿馬》一曲在南管樂隊各樂器（琵琶、三弦、簫）中，演奏同樂句時在技法、加花音與節奏上的差異，透過比較凸顯出二絃的演奏語法。在最後一章中總結前三章的分析，闡述二絃對於《八駿馬》的演奏詮釋，並對於加花音、加花變奏與技巧的演奏法詳加敘述。透過此南管二絃演奏語法的研究，希冀能拓展筆者的演奏思維，並能更有邏輯性的使用加花以及安排演奏技法，進而提昇演奏整體的表現力。關鍵字：南管、八駿馬、二絃、演奏語法

Taking a case study of nanguan repertoire “Bajunma,” this study examines the improvisations and performance techniques of nanguan erxian. Si, Mei, Zou, and Gui are the four major suites of nanguan music, and Bajunma—also known as Zouma— is in Zou suite, and considered as the representative repertoire of nanguan erxian. Due to the instrumental structure and mechanical characteristics of erxian, performers have developed a standard playing techniques for erxian. Bajunma is known for the capabilities of showing erxian’s musical grammars.This study first introduces guanmen, puzi of gongchipu, and standards of erxian performances in nanguan music. Second, it analyzes nanguan repertoire Bajunma in terms of musical structures, in order to understand the musical layers, and helps toarrange playing techniques and improvisations in performance logically. The third chapter conducts comparative methodology to examine the differences of performance techniques, improvisations, and rhythms of the three other nanguaninstruments (pipa, sanxian, and xiao) while playing the same phrases in Bajunma in nanguan ensemble. From the comparisons, it highlights the characteristics of erxian’s musical grammars in performance. The final chapter concludes the analyses of previous chapters, illustrates the interpretations of Bajunma on erxian, and performance techniques such as improvisation and variations.From the examinations of musical grammars of nanguan erxian, this study helps to broaden my views in terms of the ideas of performances, improvisations, and the ways of arranging performance techniques. Finally, it helps to enhance my overall expressions in musical performances.Key words: nanguan; Bajunma; erxian; performance gramma

